The point of the matter is that each class should override the `Object#toString()` method to provide a default string representation of objects of a given type. If you do this, you won&#39;t need the String array at all. But, if you still feel it is necessary to capture this data in an String array, your code will be much simpler because of the overridden `toString()` method.
