`Scanner` implements the `AutoCloseable` interface. That means that as long as you use it as a resource inside a `try-with-resources` block it is guaranteed to be closed when the block exits irrespective of how the block exits:

    try(Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in)) {
        ...
    }

I recommend you always use this idiom when using a class that implements `AutoCloseable`.

